domain: podweb.info
author: Saturn91.dev
[-meta]

[h1] How webrings work

[h2] What is a webring?

[p-]
A webring is a curated list of pages linked together in a ring. Every
member page shows a small widget with a previous and next button. Clicking
them takes you to the neighbouring page in the ring, so visitors can
discover all member pages by just following the buttons.
[-p]

[h2] The webring file

[p-]
The ring is defined by a plain text file stored on podnet. Its format is:
[-p]

[code-]
<title of the webring>
<url to the join page>
<url of member 1>
<url of member 2>
<url of member 3>
...
[-code]

[p-]
please note that - as you maintain this webring - YOU need to provide a way for people to contact you to get added.
So the first url you enter is a page where you explain how a user can contact you to get added to the webring.
[-p]

[p] Example:

[code-]
the first webring
podnet://48932/join-webring.podweb
podnet://48932/index.podweb
podnet://78402/index.podweb
podnet://135230/index.podweb
[-code]

[h2] Adding the widget to your page

[p-]
Place this tag anywhere in your .podweb file. Set my-url to the full
podnet URL of the page the widget appears on, and ring-data to the
location of the webring file.
[-p]

[code-]
[webring my-url=podnet://YOUR_ID/your-page.podweb, ring-data=podnet://48932/first.webring]
[-code]

[p-]
The widget will show the ring title, a join us link, and previous / next
buttons centered on the page. If your url is not found in the ring data
yet, the buttons will navigate from a random position until you are added.
[-p]

[h2] Getting added to the first webring

[p] Once you have added the widget to your page, reach out to get listed:

[link file=join-webring.podweb] how to join the first webring

[link file=index.podweb] back to home
